[{"id":"VH978179","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH978176.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">How many forces are applied to the pulley-axle system, and how many torques are applied to the pulley about its center when the block is released from rest?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH978179_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram labeled side view. The diagram is a circular disk labeled uppercase M with radius R. The center of the disk is suspended from a horizontal support by string. A block labeled lowercase m sub b is suspended by a string below the right side of the pulley.\" height=\"242\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH978176.g02.png\" width=\"225\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"passage_para\">An axle passes through a pulley. Each end of the axle has a string that is tied to a support. A third string is looped many times around the edge of the pulley and the free end attached to a block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m sub b\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m sub b\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , which is held at rest. When the block is released, the block falls downward. Consider clockwise to be the positive direction of rotation, frictional effects from the axle are negligible, and the string wrapped around the disk never fully unwinds. The rotational inertia of the pulley is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half uppercase M R squared\"><math alttext=\"one half uppercase M R squared\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>M</mi><msup><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> about its center of mass.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Number of Forces</th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Number of Torques</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">4</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">2</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Number of Forces</th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Number of Torques</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">4</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">1</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Number of Forces</th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Number of Torques</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">2</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">2</td></tr></tbody></table></div>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"></p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:2\"><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\">Number of Forces</th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Number of Torques</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">2</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">1</td></tr></tbody></table></div